Stop!

68
00:05:03,770 --> 00:05:07,569
Guys, please don't fight! We're all friends, right?

69
00:05:07,570 --> 00:05:10,069
Yeah, but they're saying it's all my fault.

70
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:12,369
Who else is going to get Yuriko back

71
00:05:12,370 --> 00:05:15,669
if the Youth Detective Squad split up?

72
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:17,369
She's always alone.

73
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:19,170
Right now, at this moment too.

74
00:05:22,170 --> 00:05:24,169
Sorry, I was wrong.

75
00:05:24,170 --> 00:05:26,069
No, I was wrong!

76
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:27,070
No.

77
00:05:27,071 --> 00:05:29,169
I was wrong.

78
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:30,769
Did Conan just apologize?

79
00:05:30,770 --> 00:05:32,170
He did.

80
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:34,869
Well, everything's going be fine!

81
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:37,269
As long as the Youth Detective Squad is together,

82
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:39,369
this labyrinth is like nothing, right?

83
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:41,370
Yeah, that's right!

84
00:05:42,970 --> 00:05:45,269
It's tough to motivate kids, isn't it?

85
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,969
Shut up.

86
00:05:46,970 --> 00:05:48,369
Hey, Mitsuhiko.

87
00:05:48,370 --> 00:05:49,469
Yes?

88
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:53,169
You found human bones in the East Mansion, right?

89
00:05:53,170 --> 00:05:55,069
Which direction was the head facing?

90
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:56,369
The direction?

91
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:57,969
Let me think.

92
00:05:57,970 --> 00:05:59,569
Here's the south,

93
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:03,069
and I went into the East Mansion one like this, so...

94
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,469
It's facing that way.

95
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:07,569
The dead man was lying on his stomach, facing the fireplace.

96
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:13,069
I guess that's where the thieves ended up, like Mr. Clock said.

97
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:15,069
When a man falls down on his stomach,

98
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:17,669
the head shows where he was heading.

99
00:06:17,670 --> 00:06:20,169
Mitsuhiko already saw that the fireplace

100
00:06:20,170 --> 00:06:22,569
was connected to where the bones were.

101
00:06:22,570 --> 00:06:26,869
So, this labyrinth should lead us at least to the East Mansion.

102
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:29,669
Great! You're my man!

103
00:06:29,670 --> 00:06:33,969
Yeah, but more important is how we get there

104
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:35,769
before we become bones, right?

105
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,969
The labyrinth of Minotaur.

106
00:06:37,970 --> 00:06:38,970
What?

107
00:06:38,971 --> 00:06:40,669
Hey, remember?

108
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:45,469
The half-man half bull monster in front of the mansion.

109
00:06:45,470 --> 00:06:46,869
In the ancient Greek myths,

110
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:51,169
Minotaur is a son of a king, who incurred the God's displeasure,

111
00:06:51,170 --> 00:06:53,969
and the God made Minotaur half-human half-bull.

112
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:57,369
Since Minotaur became awfully violent as he grew up,

113
00:06:57,370 --> 00:07:00,569
the king decided to put him in a huge labyrinth,

114
00:07:00,570 --> 00:07:02,269
so he could never come out.

115
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:04,969
So that monster is somewhere in this labyrinth?

116
00:07:04,970 --> 00:07:06,470
Come on. No.

117
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:11,869
What's important is after that.

118
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:18,969
Every year, the king sent seven Athenian kids to the labyrinth as tribute.

119
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:21,569
When the hero of Athens, Theseus, heard of this,

120
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:25,169
he went to challenge the labyrinth and defeated the Minotaur.

121
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:28,370
He returned from that so-called "Labyrinth of No Return".

122
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:31,569
By using a ball of string.

123
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:32,769
-A ball of string? -A ball of strings?

124
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:34,769
A ball of string?

125
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:38,569
Right. He tied the string to the gate of the labyrinth,

126
00:07:38,570 --> 00:07:40,469
and pulled it while walking inside.

127
00:07:40,470 --> 00:07:43,969
On the way back, all he needed was to follow the string.

128
00:07:43,970 --> 00:07:45,669
I see.

129
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,069
Then, we should do the same thing.

130
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:49,669
Yeah, we should.

131
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:52,469
You ladies do not have to do it.

132
00:07:52,470 --> 00:07:53,470
Right, Conan?

133
00:07:53,471 --> 00:07:54,570
Right.

134
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:25,069
Hey look, I think we passed here once already!

135
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:28,970
Okay, then I think we should've turned right on that corner, not left.

136
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:33,469
You're all right, Mitsuhiko?

137
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:35,069
Don't you worry.

138
00:08:35,070 --> 00:08:37,270
I wouldn't catch a cold such an important time.

139
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:51,769
Don't know if this is enough, the yarns.

140
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:54,969
Well, I think it's showing how close we got to the exit.

141
00:08:54,970 --> 00:08:56,670
Let me help you guys!

142
00:09:13,070 --> 00:09:14,469
Sorry, guys.

143
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,969
Don't worry, man!

144
00:09:15,970 --> 00:09:18,569
Our job is to find a way to get out of here.

145
00:09:18,570 --> 00:09:21,569
Your job is to solve the riddle, so just keep thinking.

146
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,770
Genta.

147
00:09:24,570 --> 00:09:28,969
That's right! Every man has his own specialty, right?

148
00:09:28,970 --> 00:09:30,369
Mitsuhiko.

149
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:31,770
You guys...

150
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:36,869
-What's wrong? -The time is over now, isn't it?

151
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:40,469
No, I just solved the second riddle. But...

152
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:42,169
Hey, guys, look!

153
00:09:42,170 --> 00:09:44,269
There, that guy.

154
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:46,770
It's just straight up ahead!

155
00:09:56,370 --> 00:09:58,569
"East Mansion" -We're save.

156
00:09:58,570 --> 00:09:59,970
That was scary.

157
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:05,669
Yuriko!

158
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:07,369
-What? -What?

159
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:09,469
Yuriko, are you all right? Are you hurt?

160
00:10:09,470 --> 00:10:10,769
You jerk!

161
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:13,569
You planned to kidnap her from the beginning, didn't you?

162
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:14,669
Certainly not.

163
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:18,970
I just kept Ms. Yuriko away from the pitfall. That's all.

164
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:24,969
I just screamed because he grabbed my arms all of a sudden.

165
00:10:24,970 --> 00:10:27,069
I'm so sorry for causing you trouble.

166
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:30,269
I really don't know what to say.

167
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:33,569
Actually, it was pretty fun, wasn't it?

168
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:34,570
Oh, yes.

169
00:10:34,571 --> 00:10:37,969
It was just like a little adventure, you know.

170
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:39,869
Right, Conan?

171
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,570
Yeah, it was.

172
00:10:45,470 --> 00:10:50,269
Edogawa, I remember you were saying you solve the second riddle.

173
00:10:50,270 --> 00:10:53,169
Yeah. But we got only three hours or so.

174
00:10:53,170 --> 00:10:54,969
We can no longer see the treasures.

175
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:56,469
-Why not? -Why not?

176
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:57,569
"The tail becomes the head"

177
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:59,269
is telling us to head towards that direction, which is north.

178
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:02,469
And also, "rat" means midnight.

179
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:05,769
So in order to open the North Angel Tower,

180
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:08,669
we have to wait until midnight tonight,

181
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:11,169
but our challenge ends at 9 pm tonight.

182
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:12,570
No way!

183
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:18,669
Mr. Clock, you knew the answer of the first part of the riddle, right?

184
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,670
What?

185
00:11:19,671 --> 00:11:20,869
That's why you just saved Yuriko

186
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:22,869
and let the rest of us fall into the pitfall

187
00:11:22,870 --> 00:11:25,169
after finding the black crystal.

188
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:29,069
No. You planned to get in our way, didn't you?

189
00:11:29,070 --> 00:11:31,769
Less than 3 hours left,

190
00:11:31,770 --> 00:11:34,970
I'm still hoping from my heart that you to solve the riddle.

191
00:11:45,039 --> 00:11:49,639
"North Mansion."

192
00:11:53,953 --> 00:11:55,153
Here.

193
00:11:59,843 --> 00:12:01,942
One more hour left.

194
00:12:01,943 --> 00:12:04,542
There must be a way to open the gate

195
00:12:04,543 --> 00:12:06,343
of the North Angel Tower somehow.

196
00:12:07,443 --> 00:12:09,642
Everyone is trying hard.

197
00:12:09,643 --> 00:12:12,143
Think...

198
00:12:13,243 --> 00:12:16,742
"When the bull's horn disappears and the tail becomes the head,"

199
00:12:16,743 --> 00:12:19,242
"an angel will come down and play the flute."

200
00:12:19,243 --> 00:12:21,743
"The song of the angel is my very treasure."

201
00:12:26,543 --> 00:12:28,443
The angel is scary.

202
00:12:31,243 --> 00:12:32,742
No way.

203
00:12:32,743 --> 00:12:34,143
But if it's true, then...

204
00:12:42,343 --> 00:12:44,942
I see. Now I get it!

205
00:12:44,943 --> 00:12:46,142
A ladder!

206
00:12:46,143 --> 00:12:47,543
Somebody, get me a ladder!

207
00:12:51,243 --> 00:12:53,042
Excuse me, where's a ladder?

208
00:12:53,043 --> 00:12:56,642
You need it at the North Angel Tower, the direction of "rat", right?

209
00:12:56,643 --> 00:12:58,942
No, I need it in the East Angel. East!

210
00:12:58,943 --> 00:13:00,043
East?

211
00:13:13,343 --> 00:13:17,243
"East Angel Tower."

212
00:13:20,643 --> 00:13:23,143
-Be careful, Conan! -Good luck!

213
00:13:44,043 --> 00:13:45,143
As I thought.

214
00:13:46,843 --> 00:13:49,443
The wait is over. Here comes the flute!

215
00:13:56,943 --> 00:13:59,942
Now, what am I going to see

216
00:13:59,943 --> 00:14:03,243
when this light hits the Angel in the direction of "rat".

217
00:14:05,743 --> 00:14:09,142
An angel will come down and play the flute of the black crystal

218
00:14:09,143 --> 00:14:11,343
to show us the treasures.

219
00:14:26,643 --> 00:14:28,442
Hey, it's over there.

220
00:14:28,443 --> 00:14:30,942
An angel has come down to the forest!

221
00:14:30,943 --> 00:14:32,942
-What? -Are you serious?

222
00:14:32,943 --> 00:14:34,242
It's the shadow.

223
00:14:34,243 --> 00:14:36,242
The shadow of the angel, playing the flute!

224
00:14:36,243 --> 00:14:38,942
"The song of the angel is my very treasure", right?

225
00:14:38,943 --> 00:14:40,942
It's on the hill where the charcoal burner's lodge is.

226
00:14:40,943 --> 00:14:44,842
That's where "the song of angel" came down!

227
00:14:44,843 --> 00:14:48,342
I got it! We still got 30 minutes.

228
00:14:48,343 --> 00:14:50,143
Now let's go!

229
00:14:52,043 --> 00:14:53,543
Mr. Clock?

230
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:05,042
It is Yuriko's treasure!

231
00:15:05,043 --> 00:15:07,742
You're an adult. Good adults don't steal things!

232
00:15:07,743 --> 00:15:09,342
Mr. Clock.

233
00:15:09,343 --> 00:15:11,543
No, it's not that. Yuri...

234
00:15:14,243 --> 00:15:16,543
Do not interrupt me. There's no time.

235
00:15:32,543 --> 00:15:33,543
Oh, no!

236
00:15:33,544 --> 00:15:35,643
No more labyrinth, please!

237
00:15:49,543 --> 00:15:51,443
-I can't see! -I can't see!

238
00:15:53,343 --> 00:15:55,542
This is Mr. Gozo Isegawa's,

239
00:15:55,543 --> 00:15:58,743
Yuriko's great-grandfather's treasures, isn't it?

240
00:16:01,143 --> 00:16:02,443
What is that?

241
00:16:04,543 --> 00:16:07,442
The game is over, Mr. Clock.

242
00:16:07,443 --> 00:16:09,842
Tell us the truth.

243
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:13,342
I know you were trying to get these treasures from the beginning.

244
00:16:13,343 --> 00:16:14,642
You were Mr. Isegawa's secretary.

245
00:16:14,643 --> 00:16:16,542
You heard and solved the all the riddles

246
00:16:16,543 --> 00:16:18,442
before anybody else, right?

247
00:16:18,443 --> 00:16:19,642
Solved everything...

248
00:16:19,643 --> 00:16:23,942
Yeah, but in the same way as I did, in the wrong way.

249
00:16:23,943 --> 00:16:27,242
The fact that he told us the riddles in the evening shows that.

250
00:16:27,243 --> 00:16:30,042
I'm sorry but it's not time yet.

251
00:16:30,043 --> 00:16:32,042
If he presents the riddle at 9 pm,

252
00:16:32,043 --> 00:16:33,542
the challenger has to wait until the noon of the next day,

253
00:16:33,543 --> 00:16:36,342
to get into the North Angel Tower.

254
00:16:36,343 --> 00:16:37,742
When the challenger realized the second question,

255
00:16:37,743 --> 00:16:41,342
in which he has to go into the North Angel Tower.

256
00:16:41,343 --> 00:16:44,342
But the earliest he can get into the Tower is the midnight of that day.

257
00:16:44,343 --> 00:16:45,742
So no matter how hard you try,

258
00:16:45,743 --> 00:16:48,542
there's no way you can break it within 24 hours.

259
00:16:48,543 --> 00:16:51,042
No! It wasn't me...

260
00:16:51,043 --> 00:16:54,242
But if he really wanted the treasure,

261
00:16:54,243 --> 00:16:57,742
he could've tried his deduction

262
00:16:57,743 --> 00:16:59,642
and realized the flaw in the riddle, don't you think?

263
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:04,042
